74.heading: Dark Horse Comics.
74.title: Fierce
74.author: script, Jeremy Love ; pencils, Robert Love ; inks, Jeff Wasson ; colors, Chip Zdarsky and Steve Sanders ; letters, Maurice Love.
notes: "This volume collects issues one through four of the Dark Horse comic-book series Fierce."

"Jonathan Fierce, a profiler for the FBI gifted with psychic abilities, failed to stop an explosion which has just killed his team of fellow agents, the only real family he's ever had. The FBI wants to charge him with the crime. Now Fierce is hunted by the Feds and on the run from the crime syndicate that killed his team. Miraculously, Fierce can hear the voices of his slain teammates, giving him the knowledge and abilities he needs to overcome the incredible challenge ahead of him as he goes deep under cover into the Jamaican underworld to strike at the heart of the syndicate and uncover the facts behind the conspiracy against him."

75.heading: Dark Horse Comics.

75.author: script, Peter David ; pencils, Pop Mhan ; inks, Norman Lee ; letters, Michael David Thomas.
notes: "This book collects issues 1 through 4 of the Dark Horse comic-book series, Spyboy: Final Exam."

"Splitting his personality between 'normal' high school life and high-tech international espionage has never been easy for Alex Fleming, AKA SpyBoy, but his world is turned upside down when the local police discover a hidden stash of weapons and conclude that he's a terrorist. As the same time, Alex comes face to face with his greatest challenges ever
senior prom, graduation, and the long-awaited truth about his mother! Tossed into this volatile mix is SpyGuy, a deadly new villain gunning for SpyBoy...cleverly disguised as a substitute teacher!"
